    "created_at": "2014-09-08T13:53:10Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-09-08T13:54:48Z",
    "body": "After a bit of research, there doesn't seem to be a default Linux implementation of a trash bin. Though there is an [XDG Trash Specification](http://www.ramendik.ru/docs/trashspec.html), that most programs seem to implement. There's also the [trash-cli](https://github.com/andreafrancia/trash-cli) package, which supplies the `trash-put` command, that users might have installed.\n"
  },
